[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi, quick question: is it possible to have a Rust LKM call into another Rust LKM's function? Was thinking about pointing module B's <code>KBUILD_EXTRA_SYMBOLS</code> to module A's <code>Module.symvers</code>, as I saw in the <a href=\"https://rust.docs.kernel.org/next/macros/attr.export.html\">docs</a> that:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>All Rust symbols are currently automatically exported with <code>EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL</code>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>but perhaps that doesn't currently hold for LKMs? If I look at the generated <code>Module.symvers</code> for my test module, it's empty:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"cp\">#![allow(missing_docs)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">prelude</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"o\">!</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">type</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Test</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">name</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"test\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">authors</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"s\">\"jibi\"</span><span class=\"p\">],</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">description</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">license</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"GPL\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"cp\">#[no_mangle]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n<span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">symvers</span>\n<span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 578691733,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773247385
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not yet (the sentence for now is referring to the ones from the central crates).</p>",
        "id": 578693594,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773247867
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Ah, your link is to <code>#[export]</code>.</p>",
        "id": 578694110,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773248010
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>ack <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span> let me try something different then</p>",
        "id": 578694133,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773248018
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>this looks promising:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">export</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">c</span>\n<span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"n\">include</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">/</span><span class=\"n\">module</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">void</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">void</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"n\">EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">);</span>\n<span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">head</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">n2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Makefile</span>\n<span class=\"n\">obj</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">m</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">objs</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test_main</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">export</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">symvers</span>\n<span class=\"mh\">0x00000000</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>still need to test from the other module though</p>",
        "id": 578695160,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773248249
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yeah this works in the second module <span aria-label=\"relieved\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60c\" role=\"img\" title=\"relieved\">:relieved:</span></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{}</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">for</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">init</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">_module</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kp\">&amp;</span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">ThisModule</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"nb\">Ok</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">Test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{})</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>it requires that extra <code>export.c</code> with the <code>EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL()</code> in the first module, but I think that's fine</p>",
        "id": 578698142,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773249052
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, the <code>#[export]</code> attribute is meant to export a function for C, i.e. without mangling like you do in your example, but it does not export in the sense of <code>EXPORT_SYMBOL_*</code>.</p>",
        "id": 578699585,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773249465
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(For Rust to Rust, eventually it will be mostly automatic)</p>",
        "id": 578699639,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773249479
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(Of course you can use the <code>#[export]</code>ed symbol from Rust too like you do there, but you \"lose\" the Rust-to-Rust advantages of a real dependency between the crates, which is what we will support soon)</p>",
        "id": 578699849,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773249546
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>makes sense, thanks for the context! Just playing around at the moment so this will be good enough <span aria-label=\"relieved\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f60c\" role=\"img\" title=\"relieved\">:relieved:</span> </p>\n<p>just a note that I can't really use <code>#[export]</code> in my module, as the macro expects the symbol to be present in the <code>kernel::bindings</code> crate:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0425</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">test_main</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">22</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">22</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 578701226,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773249906
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, the attribute can be used in modules (e.g. in the DRM QR code generator), but is meant to check that the signatures matches something that C declares in a header, so if you don't need that, then it just reduces to <code>#[no_mangle]</code>.</p>",
        "id": 578707879,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773251722
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You're welcome!</p>",
        "id": 578707948,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773251737
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It would be better to define in <code>test_exported_fn()</code> in a C header file, include it in bindgen, and then use it from bindgen in your second module. That way, the first module can use <code>#[export]</code> which will check that the signature matches what you wrote in the header file.</p>\n<p>As it is now right now, you can get the signature wrong between your two modules.</p>",
        "id": 578710849,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1773252512
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>It would be better to define in <code>test_exported_fn()</code> in a C header file</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>then I'd have to write the entire function in C <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>",
        "id": 578712540,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773253050
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No, I meant 'declare'</p>",
        "id": 578717505,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1773254813
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I thought we're auto exporting everything. Is it only for the kernel crate?</p>",
        "id": 578717911,
        "sender_full_name": "Gary Guo",
        "timestamp": 1773254985
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>No, I meant 'declare'</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>will give it a try then <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span> </p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is it only for the kernel crate?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>looks like, yes</p>",
        "id": 578722366,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773256443
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>That way, the first module can use <code>#[export]</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I think the issue with that is that the <code>#[export]</code> macro will keep looking for <code>test_exported_fn</code> in <code>kernel::bindings</code></p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">RUSTC</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">M</span><span class=\"p\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">test_main</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">o</span>\n<span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0425</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">test_main</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">24</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">24</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and there's nothing I can do about that from my module?</p>",
        "id": 578725468,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773257585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>put your header file into the bindgen input</p>",
        "id": 578729515,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1773259160
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I might be missing some context then, as I have the bindings </p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"err\">➜</span><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">test</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">git</span><span class=\"p\">:(</span><span class=\"n\">master</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">✗</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">cat</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">/* automatically generated by rust-bindgen 0.72.1 */</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">unsafe</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">extern</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"C\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">();</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but the macro will keep looking into the <code>kernel::bindings</code> crate</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">error</span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"n\">E0425</span><span class=\"p\">]:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">cannot</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">find</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">test_main</span><span class=\"p\">.</span><span class=\"n\">rs</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">23</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"mi\">8</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"mi\">23</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"o\">^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">not</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">found</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">in</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"err\">`</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"err\">`</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"n\">help</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">consider</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">importing</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">this</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">function</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n<span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">test_exported_fn</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">   </span><span class=\"o\">|</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 578742496,
        "sender_full_name": "Gilberto Bertin",
        "timestamp": 1773264083
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, it needs to be in <code>kernel::bindings</code>. You can get it to show up there by <code>#include</code>ing your header in <code>rust/bindings/bindings_helper.h</code></p>",
        "id": 578745402,
        "sender_full_name": "Alice Ryhl",
        "timestamp": 1773265362
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Those <code>bindings.rs</code>, are some you generated yourself?</p>\n<p>Perhaps this is one case were seeing the code of the macro helps since it is very readable:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">const</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">_</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kc\">true</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">kernel</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">bindings</span><span class=\"p\">::#</span><span class=\"n\">name</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">                </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"n\">name</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">#[no_mangle]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">#</span><span class=\"n\">f</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>The first part is the signature type check which looks in <code>kernel::bindings</code>, the second is just adding <code>#[no_mangle]</code>.</p>\n<p>That is really all it does (i.e. <code>kernel::bindings</code> is hardcoded), and to get things in <code>kernel::bindings</code>, you need to add it to the C header we have.</p>",
        "id": 578746966,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1773266252
    },
